    "department": "Recruiting",
    "description": "WHY HARVEY\n\nAt Harvey, we’re transforming how legal and professional services operate — not incrementally, but end-to-end. By combining frontier agentic AI, an enterprise-grade platform, and deep domain expertise, we’re reshaping how critical knowledge work gets done for decades to come.\n\nThis is a rare chance to help build a generational company at a true inflection point. With 1000+ customers in 60+ countries, strong product-market fit, and world-class investor support, we’re scaling fast and defining a new category in real time. The work is ambitious, the bar is high, and the opportunity for growth — personal, professional, and financial — is unmatched.\n\nOur team is sharp, motivated, and deeply committed to the mission. We move fast, operate with intensity, and take real ownership of the problems we tackle — from early thinking to long-term outcomes. We stay close to our customers — from leadership to engineers — and work together to solve real problems with urgency and care. If you thrive in ambiguity, push for excellence, and want to help shape the future of work alongside others who raise the bar, we invite you to build with us.\n\nAt Harvey, the future of professional services is being written today — and we’re just getting started.\n\n\nROLE OVERVIEW\n\nWe’re building category defining AI products for legal professionals and the market is moving fast.\n\nHarvey is looking for an experienced Executive Recruiter to support and scale our senior leadership hiring across functions and regions. Reporting to the Head of Executive Recruiting, you will partner closely with founders, executives, and VPs to attract and hire exceptional leadership talent from department heads to senior executives.\n\nThis role is highly visible and impactful, combining deep relationship building, rigorous research, and operational excellence. You will help deliver best in class executive hiring while contributing to the continued evolution of Harvey’s leadership recruiting strategy and processes.\n\n\n\n\n\nWHAT YOU'LL DO\n\n - Own and drive end to end executive and senior leadership searches across the organization.\n\n - Partner with founders, executives, and hiring leaders to define role scope, success profiles, and hiring strategy.\n\n - Build and maintain diverse, high quality leadership pipelines through proactive sourcing, networking, and market mapping.\n\n - Deliver a thoughtful, white glove candidate experience for senior level candidates.\n\n - Collaborate with the Head of Executive Recruiting and other recruiters to align on priorities, strategy, and execution.\n\n - Manage and partner with external search firms when appropriate.\n\n - Contribute to scalable processes, tools, and metrics for executive hiring.\n\n - Provide market insights and talent intelligence to leadership to inform hiring decisions.\n\n\n\n\n\nWHAT YOU HAVE\n\n - 6–10+ years of executive recruiting experience, ideally with a combination of search firm/agency and in house experience.\n\n - Proven success hiring senior leaders in high growth, global, or technology-driven companies.\n\n - Strong research and sourcing capabilities, including the ability to identify and engage hard to reach executive talent.\n\n - Solid understanding of executive compensation, assessment methodologies, and closing strategies.\n\n - Exceptional stakeholder management and communication skills, with experience partnering closely with C-level leaders.\n\n - Highly organized and data driven, with the ability to manage multiple complex searches simultaneously.\n\n - Comfort operating in fast paced, evolving environments and contributing to process improvement.\n\n\n\n\n\nCOMPENSATION RANGE\n\n$157,000 - $213,000 USD\n\n\nDEPENDING ON YOUR LOCATION, AN APPLICANT PRIVACY NOTICE MAY APPLY TO YOU. YOU CAN FIND ALL OF OUR APPLICANT PRIVACY NOTICES [HERE https://www.notion.so/harveyai/Harvey-Candidate-Privacy-Policies-319ac3fcdd7a803bb807d5094f249922].\n\n#LI-AH1\n\nHarvey is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of race, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity/expression, national origin, disability, age, genetic information, veteran status, marital status, pregnancy or related condition, or any other basis protected by law.\n\nWe are committed to providing reasonable accommodations to applicants with disabilities, and requests can be made by emailing accommodations@harvey.ai",
